:::summary
Metaphysics is the branch of philosophy that investigates the fundamental nature of reality — what exists, what kinds of things exist, and how they relate to one another. Its questions include: What is being? Does God exist? Do minds and souls exist independently of bodies? What is the nature of time, space, and causation? As the most foundational of the philosophical disciplines, metaphysics underlies every other area of inquiry.
:::

